Hi everyone,

We are using the object API endpoint : `<https://api.hubapi.com/crm/v3/objects/contacts/search>` to retrieve an existing user by email.

We do that by adding a filterGroup to the payload as such

```filterGroups: [
    {
        filters: [
            {
                operator: 'EQ',
                propertyName: 'email',
                value: email,
            },
        ],
    },
],```
this seems to only work for the primary email. If a user has a second or third (or subsequent) email, it won't be match to the query resulting in a user not found, which leads to a bug as we're trying to create a new user with this existing email.

Is there anyway to include other emails in the filters params that we send along the way to the search endpoint ?

